<p>Today&#8217;s podcast features Dr. Timothy Leary reading a few selected chapters from his autobiography, Flashbacks. Interestingly, he begins this recording with Chapter 19, which details with his departure from Harvard.</p>
<p><strong>[NOTE: All quotations are by <a href="http://www.matrixmasters.net/salon/?cat=91">Timothy Leary</a>.]</strong></p>
<p><em>“We agreed that as much as we loved and respected Harvard University, this finishing school for Fortune 500 executives was not the place for philosophic activists bent on changing practically everything.”</em></p>
<p><em>“The State of California should be run like a successful business enterprise. . . . Anyone smart enough to live in California should be paid a dividend.”</em></p>
